	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				As one of, in my opinion, the least played classes the enchanter has certain advantages and disadvantages. At low levels they are probably the weakest offensive character, but from a fun and roleplaying<BR>
standpoint they have some cool abilities to utilize. At first get &quot;minor illusion&quot; immediately! it transforms you to the closest inanimate object ie. a house, a rug, a lamp, a cactus etc... sound useless? <BR>
you can still cast and fight but not move, it does however have the advantage of not being attacked while resting. This give you the opportunity to regain HP's and mana anywhere without fear of attack. It <BR>
is also great for pranks! Also if you want to travel at low levels enchanters get a great combination early on. Invisiblity and Gate can both be bought at 4th level. Allowing you to travel unmolested and <BR>
still return to your point of origin with no hassles. I have not advanced my enchanter high enough to know if the offense picks up in later levels but the illusions allow you to enter any city without fear <BR>
being killed by gaurds... sometimes looking like the enemy aint to shabby! well good luck fellow enchanters!
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#D6D1BE">	
		
	
