	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Enchanter could be a lot of fun, if you know how to utilize every single spells you get.  Their Pet is not bad, having someone to help you kill something is pretty good.<BR>
You will find that your pet will hit more often and harder than you.  But I recommend that you get the biggest/baddest Animation spell you could get.  When I hit level 4, I couldn't afford the Juli's Animation spells and the fightwas<BR>
very tedious and hard.  As soon as I bought that spell, I could do 8-9 combats, taking on Sperlings (they gang up), until they were are clear from the area.  Remember to buff yourself and your pet, Minor Shielding, Haze, Strength.<BR>
When you could afford it, get invis, gate, and fear.  People will love you to help them get their corpse back with invis.  The Shocking Spears and Color Flux could wait.  They eat too much Mana and does not do too much.  Once you hit level 5, <BR>
you will noticed that most stuffs do not give you exp anymore, the White mobs are hard to come back and they gang up(Kobold Scouts).  But if it's an easy kill, I recommend that you still kill those mobs that give you good coins (sperling, kobold runts and decaying gnomes/skeleton)<BR>
You could get an average of 2-3 silvers per kill.  That's a lot of money, especially when each spells for level 4 are 4g4s.  Try not to let your pet tank, they'll die way too fast.  It's better that it helps you hit.  More info, as I gather them.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#D6D1BE">	
		
	
