	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Some additional observations since posting 'Enchanter's Advice':<BR>
On animations, the effectiveness of your pet is only as good as<BR>
the spell level is close to your own level, so upgrade and you<BR>
will reap the benefits.  Animation pets behave erratically in<BR>
dungeons, 'pacing', getting lost and pulling back more trouble<BR>
than it may sometimes seem they are worth.<BR>
While illusion spells will help overcome racial prejudices, they<BR>
do not affect faction in general.  I question why someone who<BR>
doesn't recognize me under illusion would know my religion or deeds,<BR>
but that is the reality that has been handed to us, probably to <BR>
encourage the use of faction-affecting spells.<BR>
The first Evocation spell that enchanters get isn't until level 8,<BR>
Chaotic Feedback.  As a result, one of the most costly spells in<BR>
terms of mana for a young enchanter will fizzle much more often than<BR>
cast successfully, so training in evocation may be something to <BR>
consider.  This is the main direct damage spell for some time, so<BR>
your develop your evocation skill accordingly, or practice on green<BR>
creatures until you cast more successes than fizzles.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#D6D1BE">	
		
	
			</font>
			<font face="Verdana" size="1"><b>
			<font color="black">--Submited by:&nbsp;
			<a href="mailto:dhawtho@pacifier.com">Egarim</a></font> 
