	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				As an enchanter who has gone up a few levels, and has played a few other classes since beta, I wish to pass on my words of wisdom. First off I will not try to paint a pretty picture, enchanters ARE the hardest class in the game to play, and that is reflected by the number of people that actually play the class. As a level on enchanter I recommend getting minor illusion first off, as this allows you to rest anywhere without being disturbed by monsters want to gnaw on low level players. While level 4 or lower try spending yer time in the newbie playgrounds honig your skills on those decaying skeletons and whatever else is in that zone in the level 1-3 monster range. Upon reeaching level 4 get these spells in this order, juri's animation, haze, suffocating sphere, and invisibility. The enchanter pets tend to be very weak compared to other classes but they are not without thier uses. Even though Pendrils' animation pet spell makes a 10 hitpoint pet, juris is a little bit tougher and can tank a bit when in a fight. This allows you to get off an attack spell or two before the mosnter homes on on you. As an enchanter I can't stress the importance of being in a group! soloing as an enchanter, even at higher levels, is suicidal. The reason for this is that we are great at buffing our group members, debuffing monsters, and stunning/rooting monsters. Not to say enchanters can't blast, but when you compare at level 20 enchanters have only 2 direct damage spells, level 8 chaotic feedback that does max 48 damage for 55 mana and level 16 sanity warp that does max 96 damage for 75 mana, that cause a monster to go into an instant frenzy its best to leave the blasting to the other casters in the group. This never really evens out but the best thing about being an enchanter is its hard to steal kills from an enchanter in a group. This is all thanks to a spell called charm. Ever been in a spot where its pretty much free for all but the one high powered group or individual there is killing everything? No problem charm the monster that you want to kill and grab your group and run to a spot where no one is at. When charm wears off you and your group and finish off that monster with ease! Best of all since charmed monsters are considered pets, anyone else who is trying to blast a charmed monster is wasting ALOT of thier mana trying to kill something they cannot. Also upon reaching level 16 get the illusion tree form as it is very very useful. Its basically an invisibility spell in open areas that doesn't have a random duration. The only word of caution with illusion tree or other inanimate object spells is that on steep hills or by zones there is a tendancy to &quot;fall' through the map. Normally when this happens you are teleported to the nearest safe spot in the zone you are currently in, but on occasion, the enchanter will fall to his/her death for 10000 damage. If anyone has any questions about the enchanter class and how to better play it please feel free to email me.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
